Though, I've encountered a couple of small-ish issues:  (1) Many Wifi networks don't seem to like the iCam feed.  In other words, if my phone is connected to a WiFi network, it doesn't let me view the iCam feed on my phone.  These WiFi networks seem to consider the iCam feed as a security threat, so it blocks it.  So often, I'm relegated to using valuable data minutes (instead of any available WiFi network) to view my iCam feed.  (2) Out of curiosity, I turned on push notifications to see how well they work.  Good news:  It works great.  I get a notification on my phone every time motion is detected by the webcam.  Bad news:  The push notifications keep coming even after I've unchecked the option to receive them!
